            h3.mt6.
                Install

            p.
                Cozy Light requires Node.js to be installed. Once Node is
                setup, a single command line is required:

            div.code.mt6
                span.
                    npm install cozy-light -g

            h3.mt6.
                Distros

            p.
                Cozy Light allows you to configure your server by installing
                apps and adding plugins. To help you start with common use
                cases of personal servers, Cozy Light provide you with set of
                apps and plugins called distributions.

